<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>14 - Configure Cinder on the Controller Node on Atlas</title><link>https://www.javiercd.es/en/posts/openstack/curso-openstack/instalacion-manual/14-instalacion-cinder-nodo-controlador/</link><description>Recent content in 14 - Configure Cinder on the Controller Node on Atlas</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 23 Nov 2025 12:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://www.javiercd.es/en/posts/openstack/curso-openstack/instalacion-manual/14-instalacion-cinder-nodo-controlador/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>14 - Install Cinder (controller node)</title><link>https://www.javiercd.es/en/posts/openstack/curso-openstack/instalacion-manual/14-instalacion-cinder-nodo-controlador/14-instalacion-cinder-nodo-controlador/</link><pubDate>Sun, 23 Nov 2025 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.javiercd.es/en/posts/openstack/curso-openstack/instalacion-manual/14-instalacion-cinder-nodo-controlador/14-instalacion-cinder-nodo-controlador/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This post details the steps we follow to install and configure &lt;strong&gt;Cinder&lt;/strong&gt;, the OpenStack block storage service, on the controller node (&lt;code&gt;controller01&lt;/code&gt;). We include the commands to create the database, configure services, endpoints and the Nova integration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="create-the-cinder-database"&gt;Create the Cinder database&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access MySQL and create the database and user:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;vagrant@controller01:~$ sudo mysql
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;CREATE DATABASE cinder;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON cinder.* TO &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;cinder&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;@&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;localhost&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; IDENTIFIED BY &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;CINDER_DB_PASS&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON cinder.* TO &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;cinder&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;@&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;%&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; IDENTIFIED BY &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;CINDER_DB_PASS&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;EXIT;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="create-the-cinder-user-and-assign-the-admin-role"&gt;Create the Cinder user and assign the admin role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Load the admin credentials and create the &lt;code&gt;cinder&lt;/code&gt; user in the &lt;code&gt;service&lt;/code&gt; project:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>